            "question": {
                "text": "Match the following according to input from List-I \nto the compiler phase in the List-II that processes it: \n\n\n List-I \n  List-II \n\n(P) Syntax tree \n(i)   Code generator \n\n(Q) Character stream \n(ii)  Syntax analyser \n\n(R) Intermediate  \n(iii) Semantic analyser \n\n representation \n\n(S) Token stream \n(iv)  Lexical analyser",
                "images": [],
                "latex": [],
                "tables": []
            },
            "options": [
                {
                    "id": "A",
                    "text": "P \\rightarrow (ii), Q \\rightarrow (iii), R \\rightarrow (iv), S \\rightarrow (i)",
                    "images": [],
                    "latex": [],
                    "tables": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "B",
                    "text": "P \\rightarrow (ii), Q \\rightarrow (i), R \\rightarrow (iii), S \\rightarrow (iv)",
                    "images": [],
                    "latex": [],
                    "tables": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "C",
                    "text": "P \\rightarrow (iii), Q \\rightarrow (iv), R \\rightarrow (i), S \\rightarrow (ii)",
                    "images": [],
                    "latex": [],
                    "tables": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "D",
                    "text": "P \\rightarrow (i), Q \\rightarrow (iv), R \\rightarrow (ii), S \\rightarrow (iii)",
                    "images": [],
                    "latex": [],
                    "tables": []
                }
            ],
            "correctAnswer": [
                "C"
            ],
            "solution": {
                "text": "List I representing the input to the phase and List-II \nhas corresponding phases.  \n\nSyntax/Parse tree is an input to semantic analyser.  \n\nCharacter stream is source code and it is input to \nlexical analyser.  \n\nIntermediate representation is the intermediate \ncode and it is input to code generator.  \n\nToken stream is output of lexical analyser and \ninput to syntax analyser.  \n\nHence, option c is correct.",
                "images": [],
                "latex": [],
                "tables": []
            }
